ANSWER_ONE:
To integrate SSLCommerz into your WordPress website, you will need to sign up for an SSLCommerz account and obtain your API credentials.

Here are the steps to integrate SSLCommerz into your WordPress website:

Install the SSLCommerz WordPress plugin. You can find the plugin here: https://wordpress.org/plugins/sslcommerz-payment-gateway/

Activate the plugin and enter your SSLCommerz API credentials in the plugin settings.

Add a SSLCommerz payment button to your WordPress site. You can do this by using the shortcode [sslcommerz_button]. You can also use the WordPress Gutenberg editor to add the button to your site.

When the payment button is clicked, the user will be redirected to the SSLCommerz website to complete the payment.

After the payment is complete, the user will be redirected back to your WordPress site.


BIKASH

ANSWER_ONE:
It looks like you are trying to integrate Bikash, a mobile payment service in Bangladesh, into your WordPress site. Here are the steps to do this:

Sign up for a Bikash merchant account and obtain your API credentials.

Install the Bikash WordPress plugin. You can find the plugin here: https://wordpress.org/plugins/bikash-payment-gateway/

Activate the plugin and enter your Bikash API credentials in the plugin settings.

Add a Bikash payment button to your WordPress site. You can do this by using the shortcode [bikash_button]. You can also use the WordPress Gutenberg editor to add the button to your site.

When the payment button is clicked, the user will be redirected to the Bikash website to complete the payment.

After the payment is complete, the user will be redirected back to your WordPress site.
